node.description:
StockX is hosting a BreakX event on June 4th. Each StockX BreakX purchase includes four sealed Pokemon Astral Radiance packs, each containing ten cards and one insert as well as a slot to have your packs opened live during the livestream event. You can tune in to the StockX Youtube account to watch your four sealed packs be opened live during the StockX BreakX event. Your cards, along with an 80 count pack of BCW Elite card sleeves will be shipped to you following the BreakX event.

Purchasing for this BreakX is available now and will close on June 2nd at 3PM PDT. You will receive an email the morning of June 3rd with information on your schedule timeslot and details on how to join the live stream. The StockX BreakX event will take place on June 4th, starting at 12PM PDT / 3PM EDT, where all sealed packs will be opened live on the StockX Youtube account. With each spot you purchase you will receive four Pokemon Astral Radiance Booster Packs that contain 10 cards (and one insert) and an 80 count pack of BCW Elite card sleeves.

Grading: The top 20 most expensive cards with the highest value at the time of the event will be sent to Beckett Grading Services with an estimated turnaround time of 10 days. In the event there are duplicate cards which create more than a total of 20 cards, we will also have those cards sent in for grading. You will receive a second email after the break if your card is selected for grading. Your non-graded cards will be shipped to you separately shortly after the break.

Shipping: All non-graded graded cards will ship out within 2-3 business days after the break using standard shipping methods, at which time you will receive a separate email with a tracking number.

Codename: You will receive an email a few days before the break with a link to the breaking agenda. Your time slot will be indicated by your first name, last initial, and the state of your shipping address (e.g. Brian P. / Texas). Please ensure you have a shipping address on file and it’s up to date for the agenda to show your slot accurately.

NFT: As part of your StockX BreakX purchase, you will receive a "StockX BreakX June 4th 2022 featuring Infamous Wu and Breaking Swipes" NFT which will be available in your StockX Portfolio. An image of the NFT is represented by the first image above. The NFT will not be required for entry into the live stream. The NFT will not be available for secondary trading at anytime. Once the BreakX event is over, the NFT will be redeemed from your portfolio. The NFT cannot be voluntarily redeemed by the holder for any physical products in the future. You can learn more about NFTs on StockX here.

node.description:
Welcome to the world of Pokemon — Again! Relive the Sinnoh adventure in both Pokemon Brilliant Diamond and Pokémon Shining Pearl on the Nintendo Switch. Remade for the Switch, experience the region of Sinnoh in a chibi style experience with some new updates to the game to enhance the playing experience. In the Pokémon Brilliant Diamond & Shining Pearl Twin Pack, you start your Pokémon Adventure with your neighbor as you investigate the mystery of the Red Gyarados, only to encounter Professor Rowan and his assistant leaving a case full of Pokémon starters. As you and your neighbor get attacked by wild Pokémon, you get to decide your Pokémon partner right then and there and begin building your team.

From gym battles, fighting Team Galactic, and taking on the League Champion, there’s so much to do in the Pokémon Brilliant Diamond & Shining Pearl Twin Pack. Tired of the same old fighting after a while? Not to worry, the Pokémon Brilliant Diamond & Shining Pearl Twin Pack has a fun underground spelunking feature where you can build a base, excavate items, and find some cool Pokémon hiding. The Pokémon Brilliant Diamond & Shining Pearl Twin Pack features both games, fun to share with the whole family. If you’re looking to fill your Pokédex on your own, you can play both and fill that ‘dex in no time!

The Nintendo Switch/Lite Brilliant Diamond & Shining Pearl Twin Pack Video Game was released in November 2021 for a retail price of $120.

The Nike Dunk Low Valerian Blue released in May of 2022 and retailed for $100.

node.name: Travis Scott Reverse Mocha
node.title: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Reverse Mocha
node.description:
Nodding to the Air Jordan 1 High Travis Scott Mocha, the Air Jordan 1 Low Travis Scott Reverse Mocha offers a similar Mocha and off-white palette but in a reverse-style color blocking. Its upper is constructed with a Mocha Durabuck base, white leather overlays, and signature reverse Swooshes. Hits of red on the Wings logo heel embroidery and woven tongue label gives a sharp contrast to the design's neutral look. From there, a yellowed Air sole adds a vintage feel.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Travis Scott Reverse Mocha released in July of 2022 and retailed for $190.

node.name: Be You
node.title: Puma LaMelo Ball MB.01 Be You
node.description:
In a similar fashion to Nike basketball shoes that carry the renowned "What The?" moniker, the Puma MB.01 LaMelo Ball Be You boasts a vibrant, asymmetrical look that borrows elements from colorways in the MB.01 collection. Galaxy-print areas of the upper nod to the MB.01 Galaxy, while hits of lime green and hot pink celebrate the popular MB.01 Rock & Morty. LaMelo's signature "1 of 1" insignia on the tongue and insole adds the finishing touch.

The Puma MB.01 LaMelo Ball Be You released in July of 2022 and retailed for $120.

node.name: White Grey
node.title: New Balance 550 White Grey
node.description:
The New Balance 550 White Grey features a white leather upper with monochromatic perforated leather overlays and puffed New Balance logos. From there, a woven New Balance Basketball tongue label and matching sole completes the design.

The New Balance 550 White Grey released in June of 2021 and retailed for $100.

node.name: Bone
node.title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Bone
node.description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Bone features a triple white Primeknit upper with mesh side stripes and canvas heel tabs. At the base, a semi-translucent sole with Boost technology completes the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Bone released in March of 2022 and retailed for $230.

node.name: Military Black (GS)
node.title: Jordan 4 Retro Military Black (GS)
node.description:
The Air Jordan 4 Retro Military Black for Grade Schoolers (GS) for grade schoolers first was sold on the market in May of 2022.

This unique shoe model provides a modern spin on the original retro item that was created in 1989. It features a white sole and base with suede and leather overlays in neutral shades of beige and black. The Air Jordan 4 Retro Military Black (GS) for grade schoolers has mesh side panels that were designed not only for style, but also for their breathability. The model provides the feet with plenty of support for walking and exercise.

The retail price for this item started at $210 for adult sizes.

The Air Jordan 1 High Bred Patent releases in December of 2021 and retails for $170.

node.title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Supreme White
node.description:
Supreme and Nike paid homage to an NYC classic with the release of the Nike Air Force 1 Low Supreme White, now available on StockX. This collaboration adds Supreme’s world-renowned Box Logo to the side of a traditional all-white Air Force 1 design.

This Air Force 1 Low is comprised of an all-white leather upper with matching soles and detailing. A red Supreme Box Logo placed on the outside heel completes the design. These sneakers released in March of 2020 and retailed for $96.

The Jordan 1 Low Bred Toe released in December of 2021 and retailed for $100.

node.name: Black Black

The all-black Air Force 1 Low is a timeless classic in Nike's catalog of heritage sneakers.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Black features a triple black smooth leather upper with a matching Air sole and laces. Subtle Nike Air embroidery on the heel tab nods to the history of the AF-1 line. A metallic lace tag and woven tongue label complete the design.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 retails for $90.

node.name: Racer Blue White
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Racer Blue White
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Racer Blue White features a smooth Racer Blue leather upper with contrasting white leather overlays and Swooshes. A woven Nike tongue tag and heel embroidery nod to the original stylings of the 1985 Nike Dunk. At the base, a matching EVA foam sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Racer Blue White released in 2022 and retailed for $100.

node.name: Cool Grey (2021)
node.title: Jordan 11 Retro Cool Grey (2021)
node.description:
Since its debut in 2001, the Air Jordan 11 Cool Grey has become one of the most celebrated colorways in the Jordan 11 catalog.

The Air Jordan 11 Cool Grey (2021) features a Cool Grey Durabuck upper with patent leather overlays and a signature Jumpman embroidery on the collar. From there, a white midsole and an icy blue translucent outsole complete the design.

The Air Jordan 11 Cool Grey (2021) released in December of 2021 and retails for $225.

node.name: Rose Whisper (W)
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Rose Whisper (W)
node.description:
The women's Nike Dunk Low Rose Whisper arrives in a classic two-tone color blocked look similar to the original Nike Dunks of the 1980s. This Dunk offers a warm palette primed for the summer weather, with a white and Rose Whisper leather construction. Matching woven tongue labels contribute to the design's retro feel, while an EVA foam sole provides cushioning.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Rose Whisper released in June of 2022 and retailed for $100.

node.name: Inside Out White Phantom
node.title: Jordan 1 Low Inside Out White Phantom

Boasting a deconstructed look, the Jordan 1 Low Inside Out Cream White Light Grey features a light grey smooth leather upper with tonal grey Durabuck overlays and Swooshes. Orange sashiko style stitching on the Swoosh adds a pop of color against a neutral backdrop. At the base, a white and grey Air sole adds the finishing touch.

The Jordan 1 Low Inside Out Cream White Light Grey released in April of 2022 and retailed for $110.

node.name: Jackie Robinson
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Jackie Robinson
node.description:
In 1948, Jackie Robinson broke the color barrier in baseball when he stepped onto the field for the Brooklyn Dodgers in his MLB debut. Nike honored the legacy of the iconic civil rights activist and baseball hero with the Nike Dunk Low Jackie Robinson.

The Nike Dunk Low Jackie Robinson boasts a Brooklyn Dodgers color palette with a light grey Durabuck upper, royal blue leather overlays, an embroidered mini-Swoosh at the toe, and a felted side Swoosh - reminiscent of baseball caps in the late-1940s. Throughout the design, Robinson's famous quote, "I'm not concerned with you liking or disliking me…All I ask is that you respect me as a human being", is printed in a pattern format. At the heel, Robinson's number 42 is embroidered, providing a custom feel.

The Nike Dunk Low Jackie Robinson released in July of 2022 and retailed for $130.

node.name: x Vlone Butterfly
node.title: Juice Wrld x Vlone Butterfly T-Shirt White
node.description: Since its release in the Summer of 2020, this Juice Wrld x Vlone t-shirt has become one of the most popular artist merch pieces on StockX. The t-shirt features the phrase "Legends Never Die" on the front and a Vlone logo surrounded by monarch butterflies on the back. The t-shirt was released to honor the late artist's life. This Juice Wrld x Vlone T-shirt was released at a retail price of $75 USD on July 13th, 2020.

node.name: Core Black White
node.title: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Core Black White

The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Core Black White features a simple black Primeknit upper with "SPLY-350" text on a cream side stripe. From there, responsive Boost technology in the sole offers comfort and support.

node.name: Vast Grey
node.title: Nike Dunk Low Premium Vast Grey
node.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Premium Vast Grey features a tonal grey suede upper, with warmer tones making up the base while cooler tones make up the overlays. From there, a contrasting cream and grey sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Premium Vast Grey released in March of 2022 and retailed for $100.

node.name: Green Bean (2022)
node.title: Jordan 5 Retro Green Bean (2022)
node.description:
Having debuted in 2006, the Air Jordan 5 Green Bean (2022) marks the first time the colorway has ever been reissued. It arrives in its original grey reflective construction with hits of Green Bean on the tongue and midsole. At the base, an icy blue semi translucent outsole completes the design.

The Air Jordan 5 Green Bean (2022) released in May of 2022 and retailed for $210.

node.name: Bleached Coral (GS)
node.title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Bleached Coral (GS)
node.description:
Released in June of 2022, the Retro High Stage Haze (GS) for grade schoolers for grade schoolers from Air Jordan consists of a simple pattern that is a mix of black, grey, and white. This specific model has a tongue label that contains a touch of coral, which can also be seen partially on the insole.

The primary material of the Air Jordan 1 Retro High Stage Haze (GS) for grade schoolers is both cracked and smooth leather, with suede being used on the sides and heels. The laces follow the entire length of the shoe and go to approximately mid-ankle.

The original retail price for the Air Jordan 1 Retro High Stage Haze (GS) for grade schoolers model started at $170 for men’s sizes.

node.name: Diamond Shorts
node.title: Jordan 1 Mid Diamond Shorts
node.description:
The Jordan 1 Mid Diamond Shorts arrives with a smooth white leather upper with black Durabuck overlays and Swooshes. At the ankle, a traditional Wings logo nods to the origins of the Air Jordan collection. A Jumpman woven tongue label and semi-translucent outsole add the finishing touch.

The Jordan 1 Mid Diamond Shorts released in February of 2022 and retailed for $120.

node.title: Jordan 11 Retro Low 72-10
node.description:
Jordan Brand honored Michael Jordan and the Chicago Bulls' historic 72 win 1995-1996 season with the Air Jordan 11 Low 72-10.

The Air Jordan 11 Low 72-10 boasts a black tumbled leather upper with a signature patent leather mudguard and woven lace loops. On the interior, an embroidered tongue tag that reads "Inspired by the most historic season led by the greatest player ever" tributes MJ's monumental accolade. From there, a semi-translucent sole with red and black carbon fiber detailing completes the design.

The Air Jordan 11 Low 72-10 released in May of 2022 and retailed for $190.
